We recommended that:
6.9.1 The MDRRMO carefully plan activities included in the LDRRMFIP and to only include those that can be implemented immediately and regularly monitor the implementation of projects to identify and address problems which may hinder its implementation;
6.9.2 Management provide for additional funds to have an adequate allocation for the purchase of a brand-new unit, if after careful evaluation, the same is still needed;
6.9.3 The Municipal accountant to maintain a subsidiary ledger per year of transfer for the prior years’ unexpended LDRRMF balances for proper aging of the transferred balances and disclose in the Notes to FS the amount and other details of the unexpended balances as prescribed in Item 5.1.12 and 5.1.16 of COA Circular No. 2012-002; and
6.9.4 The Management revert the amount of ₱1,700,314.15 to the General Fund to be used for other social services to be identified by the Sangguniang Bayan.

