a. The Municipal Accountant-Designate provide a copy of the schedule of PPE to the Inventory Committee as reference or basis of the latter in the conduct of physical count;
b. Any discrepancies after conduct of physical count should be noted and reported by the Inventory committee to the Accountant for reconciliation and appropriate adjustments, like unrecorded PPE, recognition of impairment loss as a result of change in the value of the asset due to its actual condition and to establish accountability for loss properties in the custody of the end-users; and
c. The Accountant-Designate to transfer the remaining completed Other Infrastructure Assets from Trust Fund to General Fund and compute the appropriate depreciation for all PPE with no computed depreciation yet.

Direct the Inventory Committee to complete the conduct of physical count of all PPE of the LGU and advice all heads of offices to require their staff to cooperate in the conduct of said activity to expedite the completion of the RPCPPE;
Cause the reconciliation of Property and Accounting records after the physical count;
Require the submission of the RPCPPE to COA office for verification and
Direct the Municipal Accountant-Designate to book up the cost of the garbage compactor truck upon receipt of the complete supporting documents and to compute the depreciation of the affected PPE to reflect the correct net book value of the individual PPE accounts.

Require the MDRRMO to cause the implementation of all PPAs incorporated in the LDRRMFIP and maximize the utilization of the current year’s LDRRMF under the Prevention and Preparedness Fund and conduct periodic monitoring of the implementation of the PPAs, so that necessary interventions may be introduced at the earliest possible time; 
Direct the concerned personnel to cause the completion of Floating Evacuation Center; and
Instruct the MDRRMO and Municipal Accountant to prepare and submit regularly the report on sources and utilization of DRRMF on or before 15th day after the end of each month pursuant to Section 5.1.5 of COA Circular 2012-002.

We recommended and Management agreed to undertake the following steps to account for all existing PPE items in the LGU:
Create an  Inventory Committee specifically for the accounting of all existing PPE items in the Municipality;
To facilitate the conduct of inventory require each office/unit to conduct their respective inventory-taking, tagging (inventory stickers) and recording of all PPE items present in their respective offices and the same shall be validated by the Inventory Committee and the General Services Office;
The GSO shall consolidate all validated inventory reports from the respective offices, which shall be the basis for preparation of Property Cards and Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE);
The GSO shall furnish the Accounting Unit the copies of the RPCPPE for their reconciliation with the accounting records; and
 The Accounting Unit shall determine any discrepancies between the RPCPPE and accounting records and prepare the necessary Property Ledger to record all unaccounted PPE items.

