Enforce the immediate liquidation of past due cash advances by sending demand letters to all concerned AOs, including those who are no longer connected with the LGU;
Require the employees to refund the unexpended balance of cash advances to the collecting officer;
Stop the practice of granting cash advances in any nature to personnel on a job order status;
Stop the grant of additional cash advances to all officers and employees with unliquidated cash advances; and
Enforce strictly the prescribed rules and regulations in handling cash advances and the rendering of accounts by the AOs concerned to reduce the unsettled accounts.

Direct all revenue collectors and Municipal Treasurer to remit and deposit, respectively, their collections within the prescribed period. Full restitution of shortage should be made immediately or before the finalization of the cash examination report;
Direct the Municipal Treasurer to refrain from collecting revenues and receipts;
Direct the Accountable Officers who is authorized to handle the logbook of AF not to issue another AF unless previous issuances were remitted and not to issue AF to unauthorized personnel. Also, it should be clear to whom the AF was given;
Expedite hiring of regular collectors;
Designate additional regular employees to collect revenues and receipts while filling up of vacant position at the MTO is on process; and
Require the Municipal Treasurer and revenue collectors to strictly adhere to the provisions mentioned in the foregoing to prevent misappropriation or incurrence of loss of government funds.

Direct the MENRO to implement the standard requirements for segregation and storage of solid waste pending collections and their final disposal to the dumpsite, as follows:

Separate containers/receptacles for all types of wastes shall be maintained from all sources;
These containers must be properly marked or identified for on-site collections such as compostable, non-recyclable, recyclable, special waste and/or any other classifications as may be determined by the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board;
Regularly collect the garbage from the Materials Recovery Facility as temporary placement of solid wastes; and
Regularly inspect and maintain the cleanliness in the surroundings of the market.
